Farewell to the Garcia House! 

One of my favorite architectural masterpieces in Los Angeles. 

Thank you John William McIlwee and Bill Damaschke for all the fun times here over the years. You’ve been the most gracious hosts (and party planners) and restored this stunning piece of art to its fullest potential. It will be missed. A lot.

And it was where I first met Carl Hopgood - a magical place, indeed.

The latest campaign for Whipshots, "WHIP IT, BEACHES" featuring Cardi B, has been an incredible success, and it wouldn't have been possible without your brilliance, tenacity, and creativity.  From the very beginning, you all approached this project with unwavering dedication and a passion for excellence.  Your brilliance shone through every aspect of the campaign. Whether it was conceptualizing the theme, crafting the compelling visuals, or developing the copy, your collective intelligence and sharp thinking made it all possible. I also want to acknowledge the remarkable teamwork that was on display throughout the entire process. Each of you brought unique skills and perspectives to the table, and your ability to collaborate and synergize resulted in a campaign that surpassed all expectations. Thank you for being an outstanding team, and I look forward to our future collaborations and even more amazing work moving foreword.

Exhibiting at the iconic George and Dragon White Cubicle Toilet Gallery in 2007 curated by the Guggenheim curator Pablo DevLa Barra,  Hopgood reveals the light and the dark, the past and the present of a lifestyle of lust and aspiration. In ‘Disposable Desire’ the impermanent medium of the work, the taboo subject matter  from the lonely heart adverts found  in the back pages of the gay fanzines,  the temporary nature of the exhibition, recreates the fleeting nature of desire and etches it into the memory of the viewer permanently. 
Fiontan Moran @carlhopgood
